{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:philemon.1",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "philemon",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Philemon 1 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:1",
      "text": "Paul, a prisoner of Jesus Christ, and Timothy our brother, unto Philemon our dearly beloved, and fellowlabourer,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:2",
      "text": "And to our beloved Apphia, and Archippus our fellowsoldier, and to the church in thy house:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:3",
      "text": "Grace to you, and peace, from God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:4",
      "text": "I thank my God, making mention of thee always in my prayers,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:5",
      "text": "Hearing of thy love and faith, which thou hast toward the Lord Jesus, and toward all saints;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:6",
      "text": "That the communication of thy faith may become effectual by the acknowledging of every good thing which is in you in Christ Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:7",
      "text": "For we have great joy and consolation in thy love, because the bowels of the saints are refreshed by thee, brother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:8",
      "text": "Wherefore, though I might be much bold in Christ to enjoin thee that which is convenient,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:9",
      "text": "Yet for love’s sake I rather beseech thee, being such an one as Paul the aged, and now also a prisoner of Jesus Christ.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:10",
      "text": "I beseech thee for my son Onesimus, whom I have begotten in my bonds:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:11",
      "text": "Which in time past was to thee unprofitable, but now profitable to thee and to me:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:12",
      "text": "Whom I have sent again: thou therefore receive him, that is, mine own bowels:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:13",
      "text": "Whom I would have retained with me, that in thy stead he might have ministered unto me in the bonds of the gospel:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:14",
      "text": "But without thy mind would I do nothing; that thy benefit should not be as it were of necessity, but willingly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:15",
      "text": "For perhaps he therefore departed for a season, that thou shouldest receive him for ever;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:16",
      "text": "Not now as a servant, but above a servant, a brother beloved, specially to me, but how much more unto thee, both in the flesh, and in the Lord?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:17",
      "text": "If thou count me therefore a partner, receive him as myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:18",
      "text": "If he hath wronged thee, or oweth thee ought, put that on mine account;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:19",
      "text": "I Paul have written it with mine own hand, I will repay it: albeit I do not say to thee how thou owest unto me even thine own self besides.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:20",
      "text": "Yea, brother, let me have joy of thee in the Lord: refresh my bowels in the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:21",
      "text": "Having confidence in thy obedience I wrote unto thee, knowing that thou wilt also do more than I say.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:22",
      "text": "But withal prepare me also a lodging: for I trust that through your prayers I shall be given unto you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:23",
      "text": "There salute thee Epaphras, my fellowprisoner in Christ Jesus;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:24",
      "text": "Marcus, Aristarchus, Demas, Lucas, my fellowlabourers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:philemon.1.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "philemon",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Philemon 1:25",
      "text": "The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
